- `lshr i8 4, %x` means `4 >> x`
- When truncated to i1, this is true only when bit 0 of the result is 1
- `4 >> x` has bit 0 set to 1 only when `x == 2` (because 4 is `100` in binary, and we need to shift right by 2 to get `1`)
- So the result should be `icmp eq i8 %x, 2`

